<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://gohugo.io/" version="0.82.0">Hugo</generator><title type="html">exit code on Sebastian Hoß</title><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/exit-code/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="HTML"/><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/exit-code/index.xml" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS"/><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/exit-code/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Atom"/><updated>2021-04-19T02:41:01+00:00</updated><id>https://seb.people.metio.wtf/tags/exit-code/</id><entry><title type="html">Ignore Exit Codes</title><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/topic/ignore-exit-codes/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><link href="https://seb.people.metio.wtf/topic/makefile-help/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="related" type="text/html" title="Makefile Help"/><id>https://seb.people.metio.wtf/topic/ignore-exit-codes/</id><published>2021-02-08T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2021-02-08T00:00:00+00:00</updated><content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In case you are using a <code>Makefile</code> to define a complex build step - e.g. start database, run tests, stop database - consider using the <code>-</code> qualifier in front of your actual build step like this:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre class="chroma"><code class="language-makefile" data-lang="makefile"><span class="nf">.PHONY</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="n">build</span>
<span class="nf">build</span><span class="o">:</span>
	start-database
	-build-software
	stop-database
</code></pre></div><p>Thanks to <code>-</code>, the database will be stopped even if building your software fails, thus making sure to clean up after ourselves once the build finishes.</p>
